==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Biophotophone
<hw>Bi`o*pho"to*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>bi`os</grk> life + <ets>photo</ets> + <grk>fwnh`</grk> sound,
voice.]</ety> <def>An instrument combining a cinematograph and a
phonograph so that the moving figures on the screen are accompanied by
the appropriate sounds; -- an archaic term replaced by <er>movie
projector</er>.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bioplasm</ent>⟦br⟧
